  "body": "/kind bug\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nAzure cloud provider uses `VM.ProvisioningState` to determine if the VM is running. Which never returns true even if the VM is not running (ref: https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/cloudprovider/providers/azure/azure_vmss.go#L137). The provider should uses (and parse) InstanceView.Statuses array -- specifically `PowerState/running` status. This currently impacts taints (i.e this taint `node.cloudprovider.kubernetes.io/shutdown:NoSchedule` is never added to the node as it goes down)\r\n\r\nFix: \r\n1. Add new functioning example `GetVMPowerStatus` returns true/false\r\n2. replace https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/cloudprovider/providers/azure/azure_instances.go#L145 logic to call this new function\r\n\r\n@feiskyer ",
